$ Shell command: hwclock
@ hwclock

Read or set the hardware clock.

The → Linux/kernel[kernel's] → Linux/timezone[timezone] is set by `hwclock`.

Apparently, the → Linux/kernel[kernel] calls `hwclock --systohc` when the system shuts down.


sa:

  → Linux/shell/commands/timedatectl

  → Linux/fhs/dev/rtc

  → Linux/fhs/etc/adjtime

  → Linux/shell/commands/index[Shell commands]

